Install pytest = pip install pytest

1.Basics of pytest
    1. Any pytest file should start with test_
    2. Pytest method names should start with test
    3. Any code should be wrapped in method only
    4. Run through the command line
            1. Navigate the folder
             2. py.test
            3. py.test -v  --> more details
            4. py.test -v -s --> All logs

             * python3 -m pytest
             * python3 -m pytest -v -s test_demo2.py
             * Run through tag name -->  python3 -m pytest -m smoke -v -s  (@pytest.mark.smoke)
             * Run through thr browser -->  python3 -m pytest test_e2e.py --html=report.html -s --browser_name chrome
             * For generate report -->  python3 -m pytest  --html = reports/report.html
             * For multiple run at time = python3 -m pytest -n 2 --html reports/report.html

2. What are the fixture:
    1. It is use for prerequisite stuff like - Invoke browser

3. conftest file --> 1. user for fixture file execute in all test file
                     2. Use fixture to class level to applied for all test methods -- @pytest.mark.usefixtures("setup")
                     3. Use fixture to class level to applied for start test and end test -- @pytest.fixture(scope="class") in fixture file
                     4. Parameterise fixture

4. HTML Report --> 1. python3 -m pip install pytest-html
                   2.  python3 -m pytest --html=report.html -s


5. Tags -->
        1. @pytest.mark.smoke
        2. @pytest.mark.skip
        3. @pytest.mark.xfail - use for when test case is failed and want be shown in report




